during this period, he translated gozzi's 'turandot' and wrote the blank verse drama 'don carlos' (1787 schiller greatly benefited from korner's generosity, which in 1786 had helped to produce his first philosophical work,  'philosophical letters' and his jubilant 'ode to joy,' which beethoven was to use for the choral movement of his ninth symphony. in july 1787 schiller left dresden for weimar, in the hope of meeting men who had made weimar the literary capital of germany.   he was welcomed there by wieland, herder and others whom the duke of weimar, karl august, had gathered at his court. in 1789, schiller was appointed professor of history at the university of jena.  this was partly the result of recommendations and partly due to the publication, the year before, of his first historical work,  'history of the revolt of the united netherlands against the spanish government'. in 1790, schiller married charlotte von lengefeld, a cultured young woman of good family, who later bore him two sons and two daughters.  the following year, his health gave way under the strain of perpetual overwork and financial problems, until the intervention, in late 1791, of two danish noblemen, who granted him a generous pension for three years. he produced 'history of the thirty years' war', in 1791-93, which further enhanced his prestige as a historian.  he spent time studying the philosophy of kant , which inspired him to formulate his own ideas on aesthetics and to produce a series of essays between 1793 and 1801 on the subject.   particularly notable are \"uber anmut und wurde\", \"uber das erhabene\" and \"uber naive und sentimentalische dichtung\".   in the latter, he was the first to cast doubt on the authenticity of the (fake) ossian poems of macpherson .
